    <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr,auto] gap-12 lg:gap-20 items-start">
        <!-- Bio -->
        <div class="space-y-6 order-2 md:order-1">
          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium text-foreground leading-relaxed">
            AI Enthusiast & Vibe Coder with a strong sales background. Living with my family in Stuttgart.
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-5 text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              I'm curious by nature – always have been. I love learning new stuff. I've worked for four different companies in sales. With every change, I had to learn new digital products and services from scratch – and honestly, that steep learning curve was always very exciting for me.
            </p>
            <p>
              This curiosity led me to dive deep into AI – and today, vibe-coding with Claude Code has become my newest hobby. I'm completely hooked.
            </p>
            <p>
              I love sports too. In my youth, I played badminton and football in clubs. Still playing football once a week, and I'll grab a tennis, badminton, or squash racket whenever I get the chance. Once a week, I go jogging with my wife while pushing our two kids in the stroller. My curiosity and love for sports also led me to pick up rugby during my semester abroad in Dublin – just because I could. Not playing anymore, but I still love the sport.
            </p>
            <p>
              At Bosch Power Tools, I'm heading sales for a SaaS project. And out of curiosity, I started learning how to write SEO content with AI tools on the side. With my wife, I founded <a href="https://pferdewert.de" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline font-medium">PferdeWert</a> – a little side project where we experiment with AI and build something together.
            </p>
            <p>
              Before I fell down the vibe-coding rabbit hole, I used to read quite a bit. Bigger topics I tried to dive into by reading were: personal finance, positive psychology, raising kids. These days, not so much – the terminal wins.
            </p>
            <p>
              My biggest challenge right now? Being the father I want to be. Spending the time with my kids I always planned to – while balancing everything else in life.
            </p>
            <p>
              We love to travel – but coming back to our home base in Stuttgart always feels right for us.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

